cancelAuction(uint256).details: Transfers the NFT back to the auction creator and emits an AuctionCanceled event

createAuction(uint256,address,uint256,ui.details: Store the auction details in the auctions mapping and emit an AuctionCreated event. If there is no curator, or if the curator is the auction creator, automatically approve the auction.

createBid(uint256,uint256).details: If provided a valid bid, transfers the provided amount to this contract. If the auction is run in native ETH, the ETH is wrapped so it can be identically to other auction currencies in this contract.

endAuction(uint256).details: If for some reason the auction cannot be finalized (invalid token recipient, for example), The auction is reset and the NFT is transferred back to the auction creator.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAuctionApproval(uint256,bool).details: Only callable by the curator. Cannot be called if the auction has already started.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

devdoc.title: Zoo's auction house, enabling players to buy, sell and trade NFTs

createBid(uint256,uint256).notice: Create a bid on a token, with a given amount.

endAuction(uint256).notice: End an auction, finalizing the bid on Zoo if applicable and paying out the respective parties.

setAuctionApproval(uint256,bool).notice: Approve an auction, opening up the auction for bids.
